# Lontext is _another go logger package_
Lontext package was inspired by [Asterisk PBX](https://github.com/asterisk/asterisk) logger.

##### Features
- Lontext extends [context.Context](https://pkg.go.dev/context#Context) implementation, which allow easy use it as ltx and/or as [context.Context](https://pkg.go.dev/context#Context)
- Common/separate settings for each Lontext instance
- Auto/manual increment for "transaction" like based on prefix
- Supported output formats plain and json
- Colored output for plain logs (journalctl -a)

##### Examples // TODO move to examples folder
- Separate Lontext instance with cancel (cancel() freeing Lontext recources):
```go
import "github.com/microgiantya/ltx"
...
ltx, cancel := ltx.NewLontextWithCancel(&LontextInitParams{
	Severity: 7,
})
defer cancel()
```

- Separate Lontext instance (Close() freeing Lontext resources):
```go
import "github.com/microgiantya/ltx"
...
ltx := ltx.NewLontext(&LontextInitParams{
	Severity: 7,
})
defer ltx.Close()
```

- Plain output:
```go
...
ltx := NewLontext(&LontextInitParams{
		Severity:       7,
		UniqueIDPrefix: "apiV1",
})
ltx.LogEmergency("message")
ltx.LogAlert("message")
ltx.LogCritical("message")
ltx.LogError("message")

ltx.IncrementUniqueID()

ltx.LogWarning("message")
ltx.LogNotice("message")
ltx.LogInformational("message")
ltx.LogDebug("message")
```

